<paragraph id="FA1336BA3161D90344E26CFAFDDA18F0" blockId="28.[151,1437,152,935]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90344E26CFAFEDE1B91" bold="true" box="[199,322,404,431]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum without solid black stripe. Pronotum with small, elongated, lateral black spots including posterolateral angles. Connexivum green without spots (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90340366CD6FBE21BED" box="[1043,1150,440,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Anterolateral margin of pronotum not punctured. Anterior margin of scutellum concolorous (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90347AB6CB2FC6A1BC9" box="[910,1014,476,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
). Black spot of costal margin reaching approximately 1/3 of corial extension. Dorsal surface of abdomen yellow to olive green with brown longitudinal stripe. Ventrally end of pseudosutures with rounded dark spots (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D903475F6F4AFC7F1801" box="[890,995,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
). Male (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90340606F4AFB0A1801" box="[1093,1174,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1412,342,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,328,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. H. brachyacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
A–C). Pygophore with dorsal rim sinuous; median part almost straight (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90346E06F26FCB3185D" box="[709,815,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1412,342,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,328,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. H. brachyacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Paramere with anterior lobe truncate, reaching superior process of genital cup; posterior lobe triangular and laterally bent (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D903479E6F02FBBE18B9" box="[955,1058,620,647]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1412,342,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,328,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. H. brachyacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with widely separated tufts of short setae; posterior face ogival and flat (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90346E26FFEFCB21895" box="[711,814,656,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1412,342,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,328,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. H. brachyacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions little developed, flat, and rounded (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90345276FDAFEF418F1" box="[258,360,692,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1412,342,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,328,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. H. brachyacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2B665313161D90344E26FB6FD5319BD" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA1336BA3161D90344E26FB6FD5319BD" blockId="28.[151,1437,152,935]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90344E26FB6FED318CD" bold="true" box="[199,335,728,755]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9E3D4B4B3161D90345726FB6FD8C18CD" author="Breddin, G." box="[343,528,728,755]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" pagination="135 - 153" refId="ref24439" refString="Breddin, G. (1904 a) Beitrage zur Systematik der Rhynchoten. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 1904, 135 - 153." type="journal article" year="1904">Breddin (1904a)</bibRefCitation>
related 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D903464E6FB6FCF618CC" box="[619,874,728,754]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyacantha">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D903464E6FB6FCF618CC" box="[619,874,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Edessa brachyacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90347AA6FB7FBD018CC" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[911,1100,728,754]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachyacantha">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90347AA6FB7FBD018CC" box="[911,1100,728,754]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">E. pachyacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Here, the species 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90341076FB7FF7F1928" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachyacantha">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90341076FB7FAAF18CC" box="[1314,1331,729,754]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90341676FB6FF7F1928" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">pachyacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90346506F93FC821928" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[629,798,764,790]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tragelaphus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90346506F93FC821928" box="[629,798,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. tragelaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species are very different; 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90340BD6F93FADE1928" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[1176,1346,764,790]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tragelaphus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90340BD6F93FADE1928" box="[1176,1346,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. tragelaphus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has humeral angles developed and globose (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D903461A6E4EFD341905" box="[575,680,800,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20G</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90346996E4FFC4A1904" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[700,982,800,826]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90346996E4FFC4A1904" box="[700,982,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Hypoxys brachyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D903404F6E4FFA801904" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1130,1308,800,826]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D903404F6E4FFA801904" box="[1130,1308,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. leptacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size and spots on pronotum, but 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90345B86E2BFDD21960" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[413,590,836,862]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leptacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90345B86E2BFDD21960" box="[413,590,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. leptacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dorsal rim of the pygophore projected beyond posterolateral angles (not projected in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90345066E07FE6419BC" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[291,504,872,898]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90345066E07FE6419BC" box="[291,504,872,898]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. brachyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90346346E06FD1F19BD" box="[529,643,872,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1667,1692]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,201,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,181,1641]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 15. H. leptacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677899/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Figs. 15A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90346AB6E07FD5F19BD" box="[654,707,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[184,1412,342,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,328,1883]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 13. H. brachyacanthus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677895/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">13A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
